# UI focus timer (agent ritual)

Platform **session length / token limits are not affected** by any script; the timer only reinforces focus (terminal output every minute).

When the user asks for sustained work on **styles, visuals, motion, tokens, skeletons, forms polish, or “beauty” passes**, or explicitly mentions the timer:

1. **Once per conversation thread**, unless the user says a timer is already running: start **background** shell (non-blocking):  
   `powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/ui-focus-timer.ps1`  
   Optional: `-Minutes 45`.
2. Continue with implementation (use parallel read-only subagents for large inventories when helpful).
3. **Do not** start this for backend-only / DB / migration-only work unless the user also wants UI work.
